# Genotype Harmonization

The genotype file (CaptureSeq SNP matrix) and the phenotype file were generated by different pipelines and at different times. As a result, sample identifiers may differ in minor ways: underscores vs. hyphens, extra whitespace, or inconsistent capitalisation. If we tried to match them directly, many samples would silently fail to join and be excluded from the GWAS.

To handle this, both sets of names are normalised to a canonical form — uppercase, no whitespace, underscores converted to hyphens — before matching. After matching, the genotype column names are renamed to exactly match `PH_MASTER$NAME` so that GWASpoly's internal join works correctly. The original genotype file is never modified; only the in-memory column names of the subset matrix are changed.

The genotype matrix is also subsetted at this stage to keep only the samples that appear in both datasets. Samples that are genotyped but not phenotyped (or vice versa) are excluded. The harmonised subset is written to `geno_out` as a single CSV that all 56 GWAS runs will read from.

```{r geno-harmonize}
G <- data.table::fread(geno_file)
names(G)[1:3] <- c("marker", "chrom", "pos")

geno_samples <- setdiff(names(G), c("marker", "chrom", "pos"))
pheno_names  <- unique(PH_MASTER$NAME)

# Normalise both sets of names to canonical uppercase-no-space-hyphens form
map <- tibble(orig = geno_samples) %>%
  mutate(
    upper = toupper(gsub("\\s+", "", gsub("_", "-", stringr::str_trim(orig))))
  )

pheno_tbl <- tibble(NAME = pheno_names) %>%
  mutate(
    NAME_upper = toupper(gsub("\\s+", "", stringr::str_trim(NAME)))
  )

join_map <- map %>%
  inner_join(pheno_tbl, by = c("upper" = "NAME_upper"))

cat("[GENO-HARM] PHENO N =", length(pheno_names),
    "| GENO N =", length(geno_samples),
    "| Overlap =", nrow(join_map), "\n")

# Hard stop if fewer than 20 samples overlap — indicates a systematic ID mismatch
if (nrow(join_map) < 20) {
  cat("[GENO-HARM] Sample PHENO-only:\n"); print(head(setdiff(pheno_names, geno_samples), 20))
  cat("[GENO-HARM] Sample GENO-only:\n");  print(head(setdiff(geno_samples, pheno_names), 20))
  stop("FATAL: Fewer than 20 overlapping samples. Check genotype vs phenotype IDs.")
}

# Rename genotype columns so they exactly match PH_MASTER$NAME
rename_pairs <- join_map %>% distinct(orig, NAME)
for (i in seq_len(nrow(rename_pairs))) {
  data.table::setnames(G, old = rename_pairs$orig[i], new = rename_pairs$NAME[i])
}

final_samples <- intersect(
  setdiff(names(G), c("marker", "chrom", "pos")),
  pheno_names
)
cat("[GENO-HARM] Final overlapping samples:", length(final_samples), "\n")

